questions.question_text: Find d/dx [sin(2x) e^x].
questions.detailed_answer: Using the product rule: d/dx [u v] = u' v + u v', where u = sin(2x), v = e^x. u' = 2 cos(2x), v' = e^x. So, 2 cos(2x) e^x + sin(2x) e^x.
